'''[[directed]] [[graph]]''' (''plural'' '''directed graphs''')

#{{graphtheory}} A [[graph]] in which the [[edge]]s are [[ordered pair]]s, so that, if the edge (a, b) is in the graph, the edge (b, a) need not be in the graph and is distinct from (a, b) if it is.

